
[1]equanimity

   EQUANIM'ITY, n. [L. oequanimitas; oequus and animus, an equal mind.]
   Evenness of mind; that calm temper or firmness of mind which is not
   easily elated or depressed, which sustains prosperity without excessive
   joy, and adversity without violent agitation of the passions or
   depression of spirits. The great man bears misfortunes with equanimity.
